title: | University of Illinois at Chicago
text: The impact of UIC’s $424.6 million in research spending on the state economy is equal to supporting 4,370 jobs. In the last four years, UIC has received 624 invention disclosures, filed 199 new U.S. patent applications and produced 212 licenses.
UIC’s 16.5% annual rate of return for students shows that there are life-long benefits of attending UIC and for every $1 invested, students receive $5.30 in higher future income.
